link:labelLink.link:label: Reinsured Management Services Asset or Liability

This is the liability in respect of the Management Services Element, determined as the difference between the Policy Liability and the Life Investment Contract liability as recognised and measured according to accounting standards, that has been ceded under reinsurance. Include reinsured liabilities for deferred acquisition cost and deferred fee revenues.
Other movements in Gross CRCs over the year

Report other movements in Gross Contractual Regular Contributions over the reporting period. Include the increase/decrease in contractual regular contributions following transfers of business from one statutory fund to another or any other movements not recorded elsewhere.
Contractual Regular Contributions are the total gross premiums for the current reporting period that are accepted through direct debit, have a specific contractual requirement for future on-going premiums, have an expectation of renewal each year (e.g. Yearly Renewable term products) or generally cause a policy to discontinue on cessation of future payment.
